{
  "texts": [
    "Then we must find a Z ∈ P such that R i (x) ⊆ Z but y ̸ ∈ Z.",
    "Since not xR i y, by the R-dense property that follows from R⇔win (Proposition 2.35) there is a y ′ ⊑ y such that (i) for all y ′′ ⊑ y ′, not xR i y ′′.",
    "Now we claim that for all z ∈ R i (x), z ⊥ y ′.",
    "For if xR i z and z ≬ y ′, so there is a z ′ ⊑ z such that z ′ ⊑ y ′, then by the Rdown property that follows from R⇔win (Proposition 2.35), xR i z implies xR i z ′, which with z ′ ⊑ y ′ contradicts (i).",
    "Thus, for all z ∈ R i (x), z ⊥ y ′, which implies R i (x) ⊆ ↓y ′ *."
  ]
}